0:{"rsc":["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","article",null,{"className":"bg-slate-50 min-h-screen py-12","children":[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Article\",\"headline\":\"How to Spot Fake Deals & Scams on Temu and AliExpress (Jamaica Guide)\",\"image\":[\"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563013544-824ae1b704d3?w=800&q=80\"],\"datePublished\":\"2026-03-22T05:00:00.000Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2026-03-22T05:00:00.000Z\",\"author\":[{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"DealPlug Jamaica\",\"url\":\"https://dealplugjamaica.com\"}],\"description\":\"Protect your money with these street-smart verification techniques for shopping on Temu and AliExpress from Jamaica. Learn to read the red flags before you click buy.\"}"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"BreadcrumbList\",\"itemListElement\":[{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":1,\"name\":\"Home\",\"item\":\"https://dealplugjamaica.com\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":2,\"name\":\"Blog\",\"item\":\"https://dealplugjamaica.com/blog\"},{\"@type\":\"ListItem\",\"position\":3,\"name\":\"How to Spot Fake Deals & Scams on Temu and AliExpress (Jamaica Guide)\",\"item\":\"https://dealplugjamaica.com/blog/how-to-spot-fake-deals-online\"}]}"}}],["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-slate-500 mb-8 flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/","className":"hover:text-gold transition-colors","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-slate-900 truncate max-w-xs","children":"How to Spot Fake Deals & Scams on Temu and AliExpress (Jamaica Guide)"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-lg border border-slate-100 overflow-hidden mb-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"relative h-64 md:h-96 w-full bg-slate-200","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"absolute top-6 left-6 z-10 bg-white/90 backdrop-blur-sm text-slate-800 text-sm font-bold px-4 py-2 rounded-full shadow-md","children":"Guide"}],["$","$L3",null,{"src":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563013544-824ae1b704d3?w=800&q=80","alt":"How to Spot Fake Deals & Scams on Temu and AliExpress (Jamaica Guide)","fill":true,"priority":true,"sizes":"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 800px","className":"object-cover"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"p-8 md:p-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex gap-4 text-sm text-slate-500 font-medium mb-6","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-03-22T05:00:00.000Z","children":"Mar 22, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"children":"•"}],["$","span",null,{"children":["7 min"," read"]}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold font-jakarta mb-8 text-slate-900 leading-tight","children":"How to Spot Fake Deals & Scams on Temu and AliExpress (Jamaica Guide)"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none prose-headings:font-jakarta prose-headings:font-extrabold prose-a:text-green hover:prose-a:text-emerald-700","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"The rise of direct-from-China marketplaces like Temu and AliExpress has been a genuine financial game-changer for Jamaican consumers. But the same open marketplace model that enables low prices also makes these platforms fertile ground for fake deals, misleading listings, and outright scams. Here is how to protect yourself every time you shop."}],["$","h2","1",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"1. The \"Accessory\" Bait-and-Switch Listing"}],"$L4","$L5","$L6","$L7","$L8","$L9","$La","$Lb","$Lc","$Ld","$Le","$Lf","$L10"]}],"$L11"]}]]}]]}]]}],["$L12"],"$L13"]}],"isPartial":false,"staleTime":300,"varyParams":null,"buildId":"zygj5-HufB_6PwBOvilB_"}
4:["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"The most common marketplace deception is the SKU bait-and-switch. A seller lists a product matrix — say, a laptop — starting at a very low price. That price is actually for just the laptop bag or charger cable. The actual laptop costs ten times more. They lead with the accessory's price to appear in \"laptop\" search results at the lowest possible price. Always click into the product variants menu and confirm which specific item the price shown in your cart corresponds to before checking out."}]
5:["$","h2","3",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"2. Always Filter Reviews by Customer Photos"}]
6:["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"Paid reviews are one of the most widespread problems on global marketplaces. A seller can purchase hundreds of 5-star text reviews for under US$50 from review farms. These look identical to genuine reviews in search results. The key difference: buying fake photo and video reviews is much harder and more expensive. When evaluating any product, immediately navigate to the review section and filter by \"Pictures\" or \"With Photo/Video.\" If genuine customers in uncontrolled, real-world settings have posted photos of the item in use, the product is almost certainly legitimate."}]
7:["$","h2","5",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"3. Never Agree to Under-Declare the Package Value"}]
8:["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"Some sellers, particularly on AliExpress, will message buyers before shipping and offer to declare the package value as a low-value \"gift\" — for example, writing \"$20 Gift\" on a US$250 TV. The intention is to help the buyer avoid Jamaican customs duties. Do not accept this offer. The Jamaica Customs Agency (JCA) uses the World Customs Organization's Brussels Definition of value — meaning they can independently re-assess any package's value based on published retail prices. If the declared value is flagrantly mismatched to the item, the package will be held and re-assessed at its full market value. You will then owe duties on the re-assessed value plus a fine for the misdeclaration."}]
9:["$","h2","7",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"4. Check the Seller's Store Opening Date"}]
a:["$","p","8",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"On AliExpress, navigate to the seller's official storefront page. Look for their \"Years\" badge (typically shown as a gold crown and a number). A seller with 5+ years of operation and 10,000+ lifetime orders is well-established. A store opened two months ago with 50 orders and perfect 5-star ratings is a red flag — those ratings are almost certainly manufactured. New stores are not automatically bad, but they carry significantly more risk for expensive items."}]
b:["$","h2","9",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"5. Use Reverse Image Search on the Product Photos"}]
c:["$","p","10",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"Right-click on the primary product image in any AliExpress listing and select \"Search image with Google\" (or use tools.search.brave.com/reverse). This will show you every other listing using that same photo. If the exact same image appears across 50 different stores at 50 different price points with 50 different product titles, you are looking at a stock photo being used by multiple unvetted resellers — not a unique, verified product. The legitimate original seller will typically have the highest number of reviews."}]
d:["$","h2","11",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"6. Beware the \"Ships From\" Warehouse Location"}]
e:["$","p","12",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"On AliExpress, many products offer a \"Ships From: United States\" option. This seems advantageous because it implies faster, domestic US shipping — perfect for forwarding to your Miami address. However, many of these \"US warehouse\" listings are stocked with low-grade inventory specifically for the US fulfillment market, and the quality can be different from the standard Chinese-origin version. If quality is critical (tools, electronics), verify whether any customer reviews specifically reference the US warehouse version of the product."}]
f:["$","h2","13",{"className":"text-2xl mt-12 mb-6","children":"7. Know Your Temu and AliExpress Dispute Rights"}]
10:["$","p","14",{"className":"mb-6 leading-relaxed text-slate-700 border-l-4 border-transparent hover:border-gold pl-4 transition-colors","children":"If you do get scammed, you have formal rights on both platforms. On AliExpress, the \"Buyer Protection\" window opens if the item does not arrive before the estimated delivery date or if it is significantly not as described. You can escalate the dispute to AliExpress's mediation team if the seller is unresponsive. On Temu, all purchases are covered under \"Temu Purchase Protection\" — you can return most items for free within 90 days, no reason required. Knowing these rights before you shop means you will always have a fallback option if a deal turns bad."}]
